# PHOS Kawasaki Copy Rules

All marketing pages follow Guy Kawasaki density: big type, few words, one idea per block.

## Copy limits

- Section opener: one `.lede` sentence, never a paragraph
- Statement blocks: one `.display-md` claim + at most one `.support` line (max 15 words)
- No paragraph over 25 words on any landing page
- Detail belongs in tables, figures, the calculator, or the white paper, never in prose
- No em dashes, en dashes, or bullet points in copy
- All headings are sentence case, never title case (proper nouns like Photonic Age and TipTraQ keep their capitals; cited paper titles keep title case)

## Type classes (defined in app/globals.css)

- `.lede` — single-sentence serif section opener, 21 to 30px fluid
- `.support` — muted one-line support text under a statement, 44ch max
- `.prose` — ledes and captions only, 17px minimum, 58ch measure
- Never set body copy below 17px

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — paragraph of explanation
<div className="prose"><p>The suprachiasmatic nucleus, 20,000 neurons in the
hypothalamus, receives light signals from the retina every morning and uses
them to time almost every biological process in the body...</p></div>

// ✅ GOOD — statement + one support line
<h3 className="display-md">Every cell in your organisation runs on light.</h3>
<p className="support">20,000 neurons set the body's entire schedule by morning light.</p>
```
